==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Parliamentarian
<hw>Par`lia*men*ta"ri*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Eng.
Hist.)</fld> <def>One who adhered to the Parliament, in opposition to
King Charles I.</def> <rj><au>Walpole.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One versed in the rules and usages of Parliament or
similar deliberative assemblies; <as>as, an accomplished
<ex>parliamentarian</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parliamentarily</ent>⟦br⟧
